# Section typography (required)

When adding or editing **headings** or **text inputs** (`text`, `richtext`, `textarea`) in `sections/*.liquid`, always include **three Theme Editor settings** and apply them in markup/CSS.

## Naming

Use the content field id as prefix + suffix:

| Suffix | Schema type | Default / info |
|--------|-------------|----------------|
| `_font_color` | `color` | Empty = theme color / inherit |
| `_font_size` | `range` 0–32 px, step 1 | `0` = theme body or heading scale |
| `_font_weight` | `select` | `inherit` + 300–800 |

Examples: `text` → `text_font_color`, `text_font_size`, `text_font_weight`.  
Subtext/caption/paragraph: `subtext_font_*`, `caption_font_*`, `paragraph_font_*`.

**Split heading** (`heading_before` / `highlight` / `after`): per segment `heading_before_font_size`, `heading_before_weight`, etc.; highlight color = `highlight_color`; non-highlight segments may use `heading_before_color` when a different color is needed.

## Schema (immediately after the content field)

```json
{ "type": "color", "id": "text_font_color", "label": "Description color" },
{ "type": "range", "id": "text_font_size", "label": "Description font size", "min": 0, "max": 32, "step": 1, "unit": "px", "default": 0, "info": "0 = theme body size." },
{ "type": "select", "id": "text_font_weight", "label": "Description font weight", "options": [
  { "value": "inherit", "label": "Theme default" },
  { "value": "300", "label": "Light (300)" }, { "value": "400", "label": "Regular (400)" },
  { "value": "500", "label": "Medium (500)" }, { "value": "600", "label": "Semi-bold (600)" },
  { "value": "700", "label": "Bold (700)" }, { "value": "800", "label": "Extra-bold (800)" }
], "default": "inherit" }
```

Heading range: `min: 0`, `max: 96`, `step: 2`, info `0 = heading scale only.`

## Markup & CSS

1. BEM class on text elements (e.g. `hero-math__text`, `intro-content__description`).
2. Scoped `<style>` block: `#shopify-section-{{ section.id }}`.
3. Apply only when set: `font_size > 0`, `font_weight != inherit`, `font_color != blank`.
4. RTE: also target `p`, `a`, `li` inside `.rte` when needed.

```liquid
{%- if section.settings.text_font_size > 0 -%}
  #shopify-section-{{ section.id }} .my-section__text,
  #shopify-section-{{ section.id }} .my-section__text p {
    font-size: {{ section.settings.text_font_size }}px;
  }
{%- endif -%}
```

## Headings via snippets

`highlighted-heading`: pass `heading_font_size`, `heading_weight`, `heading_before_font_size`, etc.  
`section-heading`: add schema + styles if missing; consider migrating to `highlighted-heading` for split headings + typography.

## Checklist before done

- [ ] Every new heading/text field has `_font_color`, `_font_size`, `_font_weight`
- [ ] Styles scoped to section id
- [ ] Schema labels in English, consistent with other sections
- [ ] See `snippets/typography-settings-reference.liquid` for full templates

## Do not

- Add heading/text fields without the typography trio
- Rely only on global section color when the text field has its own settings
- Skip re-reading files (see `read-before-modify` rule)
